{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01PjRssRMzfm4PJ8jkW3GXQM","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No python, python3, or jq in the curl-test pod. It's a minimal curl image.\n\nLet me create a migration Job with python:3.11-alpine image (same as what was used for seeding) that:\n1. Reads all messages from blue via HTTP API\n2. Publishes them to green in order\n\nThe script will:\n1. GET all messages from blue using the Management API with count=200, ackmode=ack_requeue_true (peek without consuming)\n2. Sort by id\n3. Publish each to green\n4. Use the Management API's publish endpoint to send messages to green\n\nI have the endpoints for both blue and green management APIs, along with the admin credentials, so I can now write the migration Job.\n\nSince I need to run this in a namespace, I'll create it in the source namespace for consistency—the cross-namespace DNS should handle the connectivity either way.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":625,"cache_read_input_tokens":42941,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":625},"output_tokens":27,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1e987435-a63f-4a3f-ba85-880afd406aa2","uuid":"0a9853b1-bb2c-44f8-be27-fa7ddec25836","request_id":"req_011CcMPcGaCF3HmMLsK2dYWH"}
